{
  "texts": [
    "QAnon, discussed later, is an excellent example of this type.It is also important to note the distinction between misinformation and CTs.",
    "Misinformation involves specific false claims that can often be corrected with evidence.",
    "Conversely, CTs are broader narratives attempting to explain events in terms of secret plots that persist despite a lack of evidence and mainly appeal to believers [4].",
    "CTs can lead to real-world incidents, such as the Pizzagate shooting [5].",
    "In 2016, a CT emerged that Hillary Clinton, then a presidential candidate in the US election, was involved in a child sex trafficking ring based in the basement of a pizza shop in Washington, DC."
  ]
}